<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="PubMed-not-MEDLINE" Owner="NLM"><PMID Version="1">41736537</PMID><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>03</Month><Day>10</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1364-548X</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>62</Volume><Issue>19</Issue><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Mar</Month><Day>10</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Chemical communications (Cambridge, England)</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Chem Commun (Camb)</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>A novel photochemical vapor generation medium: diketone as a medium for the determination of tellurium(IV) and bismuth by ICP-MS.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>5519</StartPage><EndPage>5522</EndPage><MedlinePgn>5519-5522</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1039/d5cc07250f</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>For the first time, diketones (BD and AcAc) were used as effective photochemical vapor generation (PVG) media for trace analysis of Te and Bi. The method demonstrated excellent recovery in real samples, and the underlying radical-driven mechanism was elucidated by EPR and TEM analysis.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Li</LastName><ForeName>Yuqi</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Chemistry, Sichuan University, Chengdu, Sichuan 610064, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Zhang</LastName><ForeName>Lu</ForeName><Initials>L</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Chemistry, Sichuan University, Chengdu, Sichuan 610064, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Zhai</LastName><ForeName>Yuanming</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials><Identifier Source="ORCID">0000-0003-3042-6179</Identifier><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Analytical &amp; Testing Centre, Sichuan University, Chengdu, Sichuan 610064, China. hanjiao.chen@scu.edu